<br>
I was a totally loyal customer until recently.  The game has become a total and utter timesink post 50, with minimal gain at enormous cost of time and effort.<br>
<br>
Then I went to play Anarchy Online out of pure frustration.  The single problem they have, as far as I can tell, is that they need to learn more about networking, since the one problem they have is that they have alot of lag.  And even that was recently radicaly improved.  Besides which, when you lag in Anarchy, mobs lag with you, so it rarely kills you, unlike in EQ.<br>
<br>
Nearly every other gameplay issue is vastly superior in AO.  Classes are far more balanced. Graphics are superior to pre-luclin with a similar type of engine used.  Post Luclin I still give to AO since I've yet to see a melee in AO skewer his head for any reason.  Personally generated dungeons, complete with boss mobs and *good* loot on team missions... Not so much camping mob_x for such and such.  Loot on several creatures that is often worthwhile for the character, as opposed to total crud/vendor fodder not worth equiping or else rare as hell items barely adequete at the level they can be obtained.  The skill based system of AO is far superior to EQ's level based one... mostly because it benefits casters and melee equally--melee can get super buffs and equip super weapons relative to level, and Casters can get super buffs and learn super spells relative to level.<br>
<br>
This and many more aspects of AO are far superior to EQ... and yet I hold open my sony account, and log in from time to time on EQ, hopeing for a better experiance one day...  I just wish I wasn't constantly disappointed. <p><br>
