Another thing of general note. Tradeskills. Take pottery for example. Lastnight i decided to laquer 600 opals. Im max for the skill. Besides the insanity of having to click each component while holding down my control key the amusing part was that out of 100 combines i failed a trivial item exactly 11 times. I did this for a total of 600 combines and when done i failed laquering a trivial opal 66 times. Seems to me that some things are not so random as they make them out to be. What id like to see at least for tradeskills is things like laquering gems or making stacks of items, let us combine the entire stack of 20 items with 20 components and let the random generator figure out how many times in that stack of 20 you failed, and give you the end result. <br>
