<br>
Take the 8th coldain shawl for instance hafting to get all those trade skills up is time consuming enuff, but then adding rare drops from mobs for the shawl combines just makes it even more tedious and a pain.  I feel the 8th shawl quest would be more enjoyable if some of the necesary drops were slightly easier to get.  Take velium hounds in WW for instance.  After spending months getting all your trade skills to that point and getting to that point competting for semi anoying to find fast moving mobs that drop the pelts  on a rare uncommon chance is lame.  They should be a common drop and drop for every wolf killed.  If your afraid that means people will use them to get tailoring above 158 easily make the combine for the padding a lower trivial and make the pelts no drop to reduce farming.  The gems off the geos should be more common in drops either that up the chance for shimmerings to spawn dramaticaly.  Shard wurm bile should become a common spawn as well with all the threads you have to collect in velks.<br>
<br>
To make a quest chalanging and fun you don't need to make it OVERLY time consuming.  There are other quests as well that would be more fun if you could complete them in a more resonable amount of time.  I feel there is enuff chalange involved for the 8th coldain shawl with the last fight and the time it takes doing the trade skill raising and the completion of each part that so many parts of it don't need to have rare or uncommon drops.  Not to mention level itself makes the quest progressive.<br>
<br>
Many things in Ever quest are fun and chalanging but arn't overly time consuming.  Take the Qeynos badge of honur quests for instance, fun, chalanging for a group in that level range and not overly time consuming.<br>
<br>
There are so many time sinks in this game that could be done away with and not make a huge inpact on the time it takes JOplayer01 to go from level 1 to uber level 65 well equiped maxed AA character.<br>
<br>
Now some may disagree with me but I feel there are a lot of unnecesary time sinks in game that actualy take away from the fun of doing something. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=macfudd>Macfudd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 336<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/03 2:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Back burner</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>To make a quest chalanging and fun you don't need to make it OVERLY time consuming. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
