<br>
1) Stop killing our spells just because they're inconvenient for you. See: manaburn, GFlux, summoning mobs, etc. (kudos on the final HoH fix btw, great idea!). Also: fix resists on Rains. A 22 percent resist on a lure-based spell is ridiculous.<br>
2) Better CS. Not only more people available. What's much more important: right now, the only thing your first line of support (your guides) can do is to apologize, transfer it to the second line, and apologize again after a week if second line doesn't resolve the problem. Also: why is it that the main function of your customer support is being a police force? Doesn't it feel a bit odd that a majority of your customers is not glad at all when there's someone of your CS dept in the same zone?<br>
People can say all they want that CS in other games is even worse, I don't care: I don't play other games, I play EQ. If you guys are so passionate about it as you say, then why is &quot;good enough&quot; suddenly &quot;good enough&quot; when it comes to CS?<br>
3) What was all that stuff with the Rathe being unkillable for so long? Over here, it's all speculation of course, because no one not working for SoE knows what really happened, but to me, and many others, it pretty much looked like PoTime was still unfinished more than half a year after release. If we were wrong on that, then why block guilds at that encounter for so long? If we were right about it, then will we be seeing that again in new expansions? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.wxs.nl/~tom.van.der.veen/Sig-custom.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ganguskann>Ganguskann</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/03 3:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Back Burner&quot;</span><hr size=1> Ok Absor, this is my first and last post I'll ever direct at you since there is some chance that you may read this.<br>
